<h3> Formula for normaliztion/standardization </h3>
     <div style = "margin-left: 2em ; margin-top: 1em">
    $norm_f(x)=\frac{x - mean}{sigma}$
    </div> 
    
    <p> Formula for probability density function: </p>
     <div style = "margin-left: 2em ; margin-top: 1em">
    $f(x)=\frac{exp⁡(- x^2/2)}{\sqrt{2π}}$
    </div>

def Percentage_Calculation(data_x,data_y,val1,val2):
        minimum = np.amax(np.where(data_x <= val1))
        maximum = np.amax(np.where(data_x <= val2))
        index_of_maximum = np.where(data_x == maximum)
        index_of_minimum = np.where(data_x == minimum)
        x_list = data_x[minimum:maximum]
        Y_list = data_y[minimum:maximum]
        percentage = round((np.sum(Y_list) / np.sum(data_y)) * 100,2)
        return percentage
################################################################################################
def Percentage_Area(val1,val2):
        X_axis = (val1 + val2) / 2   
        return X_axis
####################################################################################################
def  Normal_Distribution_graph(x):
        (mu, sigma) = norm.fit(x)
        y = norm.pdf(x, mu, sigma)
        data = pd.DataFrame()
        data["x"] = x
        data["y"] = y
        data = data.sort_values("x")
        data = data.drop_duplicates("x")
        return data["x"], data["y"]
#######################################################################################################
def Fill_Function(data_x,data_y,line_A,line_B):
      minimum = np.amin(np.where(data_x >= line_A))
      maximum = np.amax(np.where(data_x <= line_B))
      x_list = data_x[minimum:maximum]
      x_list.append(pd.Series(line_A))
      x_list = x_list.append(pd.Series(line_B))
      #print("1",type(x_list))
#       x_list = x_list.sort_values()
#       x_list = x_list.reset_index(drop = True)
      Y_list = data_y[minimum:maximum]
      y_min = np.interp(line_A,data_x, data_y)
      y_max = np.interp(line_B,data_x, data_y)
      Y_list.append(pd.Series([y_min]))
      Y_list = Y_list.append(pd.Series([y_max]))
      data = pd.DataFrame()
      data["x"] = x_list
      data["y"] = Y_list
      data = data.sort_values("x")
      data = data.reset_index(drop = True)
      return data["x"] , data["y"]
